comment.text: "Used in a UI component to display a notification when the form is partially filled."

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'نموذج مكتمل جزئيًا' (Namuthaj muktamil juz'iyyan) literally translates to 'Partially completed form'. While conveying a similar concept, the English phrase 'Filled out part of form' implies action taken by the user. 'Partially completed form' implies the form has been completed by some process, not necessarily a user action.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ملؤ جزء من النموذج (Mil'u juz'un min an-namuthaj)

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Czech translation 'Vyplněná část formuláře' literally translates to 'Filled part of the form'. While understandable, it's not the most natural or idiomatic way to express 'Filled out part of form' in Czech. A more accurate and natural translation would convey the action of filling out.

The translation 'Συμπληρωμένο μέρος της φόρμας' (Sympliroμένο μέρος tis formás) is a literal translation and doesn't convey the meaning of 'Filled out part of form' in a natural Greek way. It suggests that *part* of the form is completed. A more accurate and idiomatic translation would capture the implication that some data has been entered.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Έχουν συμπληρωθεί μερικά πεδία της φόρμας.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While "Formulario parcialmente rellenado" is understandable, a more natural and common Spanish translation of "Filled out part of form" would be "Se ha completado parcialmente el formulario" or "Se ha llenado parcialmente el formulario". "Rellenado" isn't typically used in this context.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Se ha completado parcialmente el formulario.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Partie du formulaire remplie' is technically correct but lacks the nuance of 'partially filled' which implies incompleteness. A more accurate translation would convey that the form is not fully completed.

The translation 'Ձևաթղթի լրացված հատված։' is a literal translation of 'part of form filled out' and doesn't quite capture the intended meaning of 'Filled out part of form.' It suggests a section *within* the form is filled, rather than the process of filling part of it.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider a phrasing like 'Մասամբ լրացված ձև։' or 'Ձևի մաս լրացվել է։' which conveys the idea of 'part of the form filled out'.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While 'Modulo parzialmente compilato' is understandable, a more natural and accurate translation of 'Filled out part of form' would be 'Completata una parte del modulo' or 'Compilata una parte del modulo'. The current translation is a bit literal and sounds less fluent.

The Japanese translation "一部しか記入していないフォーム。" is a literal translation but sounds unnatural and overly verbose. A more natural and concise translation would better convey the meaning of 'Filled out part of form'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: フォームの一部を記入しました。 (Fōmu no ichibu o kijun shimashita.) or フォームを一部記入しました。(Fōmu o ichibu kijun shimashita.)

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Lao translation 'ຕື່ນຂໍ້ມູນສ່ວນຫນຶ່ງຂອງແບບຟອມແລ້ວ' literally translates to 'Woke up part of the form already.' which doesn't accurately convey the meaning of 'Filled out part of form.' A more appropriate translation would describe the action of filling out.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ເລື່ອນຂໍ້ມູນສ່ວນຫນຶ່ງຂອງແບບຟອມແລ້ວ (Luean khomun suan neung khong baep form laeo) - which means 'Moved/Entered data part of the form already'.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Veidlapas aizpildītā daļa' is a literal translation of 'Part of form filled out'. A more natural and idiomatic Latvian translation for 'Filled out part of form' would be something like 'Daļa aizpildīta veidlapa' or 'Aizpildīta veidlapas daļa'.

The translation 'Wypełniona część formularza' literally translates to 'Filled part of the form'. It lacks the nuance of 'partially filled'. A better translation would convey the meaning of 'partially filled'.

The Romanian translation 'Formularul este completat parțial' translates literally to 'The form is partially completed.' While understandable, it's not the most natural or idiomatic way to convey 'Filled out part of form.' A more natural translation would emphasize the action of filling, not the state of being completed.
The word 'පෝරමයේ' (poramayae) is a proper transliteration of 'form'.
The word 'කොටසක්' (kotasak) is a proper transliteration of 'part'.
The word 'පිර' (pira) is a proper transliteration of 'filled'.
The word 'ඇත' (atha) is a proper transliteration of 'is'.

While technically correct, the translation 'පෝරමයේ කොටසක් පිර වී ඇත' (poramayae kotasak pira ve atha) can sound somewhat formal or stiff. A more natural and commonly used phrasing might be preferred depending on the context.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider a more colloquial phrasing like 'පෝරමයේ කොටස පිරවී තිබේ' (poramayae kotasak pira wei thibei).

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Slovak translation 'Vyplnená časť formulára' translates more literally as 'Filled part of the form' rather than 'Part of form filled out'. While understandable, it doesn't fully capture the nuance of the English original.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Vyplnená časť formulára (alternatively: Časť formulára bola vyplnená.)

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Izpolnjen del obrazca' while literally meaning 'Filled part of form' doesn't quite capture the nuance of 'Filled out part of form.' It suggests a portion *is* filled, rather than the action of having filled part of it.

The translation 'Делимично попуњен формулар' while technically correct, doesn't quite capture the nuance of 'partially filled out form.' A more natural Serbian translation would prioritize flow and common phrasing. The current translation feels slightly literal.

The translation 'Delimično popunjen formular' doesn't accurately convey the meaning of 'Filled out part of form.' A more accurate translation would emphasize the partial completion. 'Delimično ispunjen formular' is a better option.

The translation 'Заповнена частина форми' literally translates to 'Filled part of the form.' It doesn't convey the meaning of 'partially filled'. A more accurate translation would indicate that not all fields were filled.

The translation 'Đã điền vào một phần của biểu mẫu' while technically correct, is a bit literal and doesn't flow as naturally as it could. A more natural phrasing would be 'Đã điền một phần biểu mẫu.' or 'Điền một phần biểu mẫu.'
